# 2) One-Shot Prompting

**Definition:** Provide **one example** to set format/style, then request the new output.

**Finance (Example â†’ New Task):**
Example format: â€œ**Finding:** X. **Evidence:** Y. **Impact:** Z. **Action:** A.â€
â€œUsing the format above, assess **currency risk** for our euro-denominated revenues (â‚¬40M; natural hedge 30%).â€

**Sales:**
Example cold email (3 sentences, CTA link).
â€œUsing that tone/length, write to a **VP of Ops in logistics** about our route-optimization tool; include a calendar CTA.â€

**IT:**
Example change record (Title/Scope/Risk/Backout).
â€œCreate a change record for **firewall rule cleanup** across DMZ; include validation tests.â€

**Risk & Compliance:**
Example control statement (Objective/Control/Owner/Frequency/Evidence).
â€œAuthor a control for **joiner-mover-leaver** access revocation in <24h.â€

**HR:**
Example job summary (Role/Impact/Outcomes/Skills).
â€œWrite a summary for **Senior Data Engineer (Marketing Analytics)**.â€

**Legal:**
Example issue log entry (Clause/Risk/Ask/Counterproposal/Status).
â€œLog issues for **limitation of liability** and **data processing** in the attached vendor MSA (assume standard terms).â€

