# 7) Instruction-Based Prompting

**Definition:** Give **crisp constraints** on format, length, criteria, and tone.

**Finance:**
â€œProvide a **5-bullet** portfolio **risk summary** (max 12 words/bullet). Use **measurable** language; include **1 action** and **1 caveat**.â€

**Sales:**
â€œWrite a **4-step email sequence** (subject + 2 sentences + CTA). Keep **<60 chars** subjects; avoid buzzwords.â€

**IT:**
â€œOutput a **YAML** with 3 envs (dev/stage/prod) for **rate limits**. Include **burst**, **sustained**, **429 policy**.â€

**Risk & Compliance:**
â€œCreate a **RACI table** (markdown) for **annual policy review**. Roles: Legal, Risk, IT, HR, Business.â€

**HR:**
â€œWrite a **competency matrix** (table) for **Data Analyst** L1-L3; columns: Skills, Behaviors, Measurement.â€

**Legal:**
â€œSummarize **indemnity clause** risks in **3 bullets**, then give **2 alternative wordings**.â€

---

# 8) Self-Consistency Prompting

**Definition:** Generate **multiple options/paths**, then **select** the most reliable.

**Finance:**
â€œPropose **3 hedging strategies** for rate risk (swaps, futures, barbell). Evaluate each; **pick one** with rationale.â€

**Sales:**
â€œList **3 ICP definitions** for our AI copilot. Score TAM, urgency, competition; **recommend one**.â€

**IT:**
â€œOffer **3 migration plans** (big bang, phased, strangler). Compare risk/cost; **choose best**.â€

**Risk & Compliance:**
â€œSuggest **3 monitoring KRIs** for model risk. Rate detectability and false positives; **select primary**.â€

**HR:**
â€œDesign **3 interview loops** for Staff Engineer. Compare signal quality/time; **recommend**.â€

**Legal:**
â€œDraft **3 fallback positions** on **liability cap** (fees-based variants). **Select** the most defensible.â€

---

# 9) Decomposition (Break-Down) Prompting

**Definition:** Ask the model to **split a complex task** into sub-tasks, then solve.

**Finance:**
â€œBreak down the **rate-shock analysis** into steps (data, math, sensitivities, report). Execute each step briefly; consolidate the findings.â€

**Sales:**
â€œDecompose **pipeline quality review** into inputs (coverage, aging, stage conversion). Produce a checklist and next actions.â€

**IT:**
â€œBreak down **DR strategy** for a 3-tier app (RPO/RTO, backups, failover tests). Deliver a 90-day plan.â€

**Risk & Compliance:**
â€œDecompose **AI compliance** (data lineage, bias testing, human-in-the-loop, logging). Produce a minimal controls set.â€

**HR:**
â€œBreak down **attrition analysis** (cohorts, tenure, role, manager effects). Provide a storyline for ELT.â€

**Legal:**
â€œDecompose **cross-border data transfer** compliance (lawful basis, SCCs, DTI, TOMs). Output a checklist.â€

---

# 10) Retrieval/Context-Grounded Prompting

**Definition:** Provide **context** (docs/data) and ask the model to **only** use it, stating assumptions if gaps remain.

**Finance:**
â€œUsing the attached **portfolio summary** (durations, weights), estimate the **+1% rate shock** impact. If issuer details are missing, assume IG, spread +10 bps. Show calc table and a 3-point mitigation plan.â€

**Sales:**
â€œUsing the **Q2 win/loss report**, synthesize **top 5 reasons** for losses and craft **2 counter-plays** per reason.â€

**IT:**
â€œFrom the **runbook PDFs**, generate a **â€˜first 15 minutesâ€™** incident checklist for **API 5xx spikes**.â€

**Risk & Compliance:**
â€œUsing our **policy library**, map controls to **NIST CSF** categories; output a **gap list**.â€

**HR:**
â€œBased on the **employee survey**, create a **3-theme action plan** with owners and 60-day milestones.â€

**Legal:**
â€œFrom the **vendor contract** provided, extract **termination** and **data security** obligations into a 2-column table (Clause â†’ Obligation).â€

